quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  9,127,"And whenever a sūrah is revealed, they look at each other, [as if saying], "
  9,128,"There has certainly come to you a Messenger from among yourselves. Grievous to him is what you suffer; [he is] concerned over you [i.e., your guidance] and to the believers is kind and merciful."
  9,129,"But if they turn away, [O Muḥammad], say, "
  10,85,"So they said, "
  10,86,"And save us by Your mercy from the disbelieving people."
  10,87,"And We inspired to Moses and his brother, ",footnotes:1:In order that they might pray therein unseen by their enemy.
  11,52,"And O my people, ask forgiveness of your Lord and then repent to Him. He will send [rain from] the sky upon you in showers and increase you in strength [added] to your strength. And do not turn away, [being] criminals."
  11,53,"They said, "
  11,54,"We only say that some of our gods have possessed you with evil [i.e., insanity]."
  12,13,"[Jacob] said, "
  12,14,"They said, "
  12,15,"So when they took him [out] and agreed to put him into the bottom of the well...{1} But We inspired to him, ",footnotes:1:The conclusion of this sentence is estimated to be "...they tormented him."